# A request the allocator cannot possibly satisfy must die loudly, not deref a
# null block. 1e18 elements * 8 bytes = 8e18 bytes: under the size_t wrap cap
# tycho_cap_check enforces (SIZE_MAX/8 = 2305843009213693951), so it passes the
# range check and reaches the real malloc -- which cannot return 8 EB on any
# 64-bit host (it exceeds the 128 TiB user address space, overcommit or not).
# tychoc0's blk_get used to ignore the NULL and SIGSEGV (exit 139) here.
fn main():
    a := []int
    reserve(a, 1000000000000000000)
    push(a, 1)
    print(str(len(a)))
